This paper explores the syntactic abilities of RNNs, which is a topic that falls under the category of natural language processing (NLP). Therefore, cs.CL (Computation and Language) is the most likely sub-category. The paper also discusses multi-task learning, which is a common technique in machine learning, and can be applied to various sub-fields of computer science. Therefore, cs.LG (Machine Learning), cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence), and cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing) are also likely sub-categories. Finally, the paper mentions CCG supertagging, which is a task related to parsing and syntax, and can be categorized under cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition).
